  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 720 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/japanese-style-panko-pork-cutlets-5a2b0d2905346868a85a06e2
servings: 2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
---

Place @Jasmine Rice{1%cup}, 1 1/2 cups water, and a @salt{pinch} in a small #pot{}. Cover and bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until meal is ready.

Meanwhile, place @Panko Breadcrumbs{1%cup} on a #plate{}. Pat @Pork Cutlets{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season all over with @salt and @pepper. Brush evenly with @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}. Dip pork one piece at a time into panko, flipping to coat and pressing to adhere.

Heat a thin layer of @Vegetable Oil{4%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over high heat (we used 2 TBSP; use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add half the pork to pan and cook until panko is golden brown and crisp, about ~{3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate and set aside. Repeat with remaining pork.

> TIP: Add more oil if pan seems dry after first batch.

Wash and dry all produce. Slice @Persian Cucumber{6}(sliced into thin rounds). Trim, then thinly slice @Scallions{4}(keeping greens and whites separate). Toss together cucumbers, @Sesame Oil{2%tablespoon}, scallion whites, half the @Sesame Seeds{2%tablespoon}, @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Sugar{2%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of @salt in a #medium bowl{}.

Mix together @Hoisin Sauce{4%tablespoon}, @Garlic Powder{2%teaspoon}, @Ketchup{4%tablespoon}, and @Soy Sauce{4%teaspoon} (we sent more) in a #small bowl{}, stirring until thoroughly combined.

> Our chefs adapted this slightly, using sour cream as extra insurance to make sure that the crumbs stick to the thin-cut pork. That change makes a world of difference, guaranteeing a crispy, golden brown crust.

Slice pork into strips. Divide rice and cucumbers between plates, then arrange pork on top of rice. Drizzle pork with sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds.